The statement by the President of the United States expresses support for the end of former President Laurent Gbagbo's illegitimate claim to power in Cote d'Ivoire. It emphasizes the victory for the democratic will of the Ivoirian people and the opportunity for them to rebuild their country and solidify their democracy. The United States and the international community have strongly supported the results of Cote d'Ivoire's democratic election and the right of the Ivoirian people to determine their own destiny. The statement commends the United Nations Operation in Cote d'Ivoire and French forces for protecting civilians. It calls for reconciliation and rebuilding, with President Ouattara needing to govern on behalf of all the people, including those who did not vote for him. It also urges all militia groups to disarm and acknowledges the need for accountability for violence and crimes committed. The international community is called upon to continue supporting the people of Cote d'Ivoire in their transition to a more hopeful and democratic future.